1. The Core Monitoring Stack (Metrics & Alerting)

    kube-prometheus-stack (Prometheus + Grafana + Alertmanager):

        Prometheus: Scrapes metrics from node exporters (CPU/Memory/Disk), Kubernetes system components (kubelet, API server), and NGINX Ingress controller endpoints.

        Grafana: Visualizes golden signals (Latency, Traffic, Errors, Saturation).

        Alertmanager: Triggers alerts via Slack/PagerDuty for critical events (e.g., PodCrashLooping, High CPU/Memory throttling, 5xx HTTP response spikes).

2. Centralized Logging

       Elasticsearch: Allows querying application logs directly inside Grafana to trace errors when HTTP 5xx codes spike.
